The paper deals with the reachability problem in vector addition systems with states (VASS), which is a central problem in formal verification and concurrency theory. This makes it likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the study of the complexity of the reachability problem, which suggests that it could also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories. The use of integer fractions in the third result suggests a possible connection to Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), while the use of Petri nets and concurrency models suggests a possible connection to Programming Languages (cs.PL).
